{"lemma":"مِغْفَرٌ","slug":"مِغْفَرٌ","root":"غ.ف.ر","root_slug":"غ-ف-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ف-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32121"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D8%BA%D9%92%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32121","headword_ar":"مِغْفَرٌ","root":"gfr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is worn beneath the helmet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of mail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaradN","text_ar":"زَرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woven"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diroE","text_ar":"دِرْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coat of mail"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"according to the size of the head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worn beneath the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of cap called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalanosuwap","text_ar":"قَلَنْسُوَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"migofarapN","text_ar":"مِغْفَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gifaArapN","text_ar":"غِفَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raforaf","text_ar":"رَفْرَف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pendent appertenance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the helmet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of mail,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2275},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalaqN","text_ar":"حَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilaqN","text_ar":"حِلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in different copies of the K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which an armed man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to some lexicons, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wears in the manner of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qinaAE","text_ar":"قِنَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yataqan~aEu bihaA","text_ar":"يَتَقَنَّعُ بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"); as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"migofarapN","text_ar":"مِغْفَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gifaArapN","text_ar":"غِفَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) accord. to ISh, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"migofar","text_ar":"مِغْفَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of mail"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalaqN","text_ar":"حَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which a man puts beneath the helmet, hanging down upon the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sometimes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"he says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalanosuwap","text_ar":"قَلَنْسُوَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except that it is more ample; a man throws it upon his head, and it reaches to the coat of mail; then the helmet is put on over it; and this"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mgfr","text_ar":"مغفر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hangs down upon the shoulders: sometimes, also, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mgfr","text_ar":"مغفر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a covering for the head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diybaAj","text_ar":"دِيبَاج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silk brocade"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the cloth called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaz~","text_ar":"خَزّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath the helmet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to “ the Book of the Coat of Mail and the Helmet, ” by AO,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"migofarN","text_ar":"مِغْفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gifaArapN","text_ar":"غِفَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"are names applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion of mail"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forming a headcovering"},{"kind":"text","text":"], which is also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasobigapN","text_ar":"تَسْبِغَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and sometimes the rings are exposed to view; and sometimes they line them within, and cover them externally, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diybaAj","text_ar":"دِيبَاج"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaz~","text_ar":"خَزّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the kind of silk stuff called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bizoyawon","text_ar":"بِزْيَوْن"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and they stuff it with something"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H$~whA bmA kAn","text_ar":"حشّوها بما كان"},{"kind":"text","text":");"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and sometimes they make above it a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawonas","text_ar":"قَوْنَس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tapering top"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of silver"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (TA:) the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"migofar","text_ar":"مِغْفَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"helmet"},{"kind":"text","text":"itself. (Mgh.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mugofuwrN","text_ar":"مُغْفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%85%D8%BA%D9%81%D8%B1/","headword_ar":"مغفر","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_21","lexicon_en":"Muḥammad al-Fattinī, Majmaʿ Biḥār al-Anwār fī Gharāʾib al-Tanzīl wa Laṭāʾif al-Akhbār (d. 1578 CE)","lexicon_ar":"مجمع بحار الأنوار للفَتِّنيّ","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=35509#52bd81","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">[مغفر]</span><span> ك: فيه: دخل وعلى رأسه \"المغفر\"، هو بكسر ميم: زرد ينسج على قدر الرأس يلبس تحت القلنوسة وهو موضع التمسك إذ لو أحرم لكشف رأسه- ومر في غ. ط: وهو وقاية للرأس وكان ذا أول دخوله ثم أزاله ووضع العمامة فلا ينافي ح العمامة.</span>"}]}}